title: Thank God
lyrics:
Baby, I've been overdosing on your love
An explosion like they did back in the days
Baby, I've been overthinking 'bout our drinks
We've been drinking, I just don't know what to say
It's your touch that keeps me grounded

The sounds I want surrounded

Around me for the rest of my life

The things that make you special

Think you deserve a medal

For getting me, you're taking me high



All I wanna say is thank God for you

And all the other things you do

Thank God for you

All I wanna say is thank God for you

Hope you feel the same way too

Thank God for you



(All I wanna say is thank God

And all the other things

Thank God

Hope you feel the same way too

All I wanna say is thank God

And all the other things

Thank God

Hope you feel the same way too)



Baby, I've been overspending

On the things that we're ending

'Cause I just don't want them to

Baby, I've been overlooking, all the things in a box

'Cause I know we know what to do



It's your touch that keeps me grounded

The sounds I want surrounded

Around me for the rest of my life



All I wanna say is thank God for you

And all the other things you do

Thank God for you

All I wanna say is thank God for you

Hope you feel the same way too

Thank God for you



(All I wanna say is thank God

And all the other things

Thank God

Hope you feel the same way too

All I wanna say is thank God

And all the other things

Thank God

Hope you feel the same way too)
